^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And most of you do not play that. A 2@C bid by responder guarantees at least one 4 card major. So, if you as the 1N opener bid 1 of the majors and responder puts you back in NT, you know for sure that responder has the other major. On this hand, once I bid 2N, he knows I have 4 spades and 8 or 9 points. In general Kia has a number of choices.|
