NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|A couple of other points about Stayman. If partner bids Stayman and you have both hearts and spades, the usual treatment is to bid hearts first. Also, if you play 4 way transfers where 2N is not an 8-9 invitational hand (it is a diamond transfer) you have to have a way to show the 8-9 invitational hand that those who do not play transfers would bid 2N with. |
PG| ***** 48 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The way you do that is you bid Stayman and then bid 2N over whatever partner bids. In that case, 2@C does not guarantee a 4-card major. However, if you do play 4 way transfers, and the auction goes as it did here, 1N-2@C-2@H-?, 2@C does not absolutely promise a 4-card major. If you have 4 spades, you have to bid 2@S. Further, if you bid 2N over 2@H that denies holding 4 spades and simply shows the invitational hand. If I were playing with many of my partners with whom I play 4 way transfers, I would have bid 2@S over 2@H to show my 4 card spade suit. And Kia would bid 4@S.|
